  "prompt": "How do you download YouTube videos using VLC Media Player?",
  "response": "To download YouTube videos using VLC Media Player, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open VLC Media Player\n\n2. Go to Media > Open Network Stream\n\n3. Paste the YouTube video URL\n\n4. Click \"Play\"\n\n5. Go to Tools > Preferences\n\n6. Under \"Input/Codecs\", check \"Show more options\"\n\n7. Navigate to \"Demuxers\" > \"HTTP\"\n\n8. Enable \"Fetch Metadata\"\n\n9. Go to the \"Location\" where you want to save the video\n\n10. Press Ctrl+S or go to Media > Convert/Save\n\n11. Select the video and choose a destination folder\n\n12. Select an output format and video quality\n\n13. Click \"Start\"\n\nNote: While VLC can help you save videos, it's recommended to use dedicated YouTube downloading tools or websites for more reliable results, as YouTube's terms of service discourage video downloading.\n\nAlways respect copyright laws and the content creator's rights when downloading videos.",
